📘 Unibar Plus – Complete Usage Documentation

Unibar Plus is a simple script that allows you to create buttons with custom functions in Roblox Unibar.
Below, you will see a detailed guide on how to use it

==[=====================÷÷÷====================]==

🔘 Creating Buttons

Buttons are created using the MakeButton event.

⚙️ Syntax (oneclick)

game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")["Unibar Plus API"].MakeButton:Fire("oneclick", Name, SelectedImageId, SelectedFunction)

⚙️ Syntax (twoclick)

game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")["Unibar Plus API"].MakeButton:Fire("twoclick", Name, SelectedImageId, UnSelectedImageId, SelectedFunction, UnSelectedFunction)

📃 Parameters

Parameter	Description 👇

• Type:	Can be "oneclick" or "twoclick"
• Name:	Unique name of the button
• SelectedImageId:	Image ID used when the button is selected
• UnSelectedImageId:	Image ID used when the button is not selected (only for twoclick)
• SelectedFunction:	Function executed when selected
• UnSelectedFunction:	Function executed when deselected (only for twoclick)

🖼️ Obtaining an image ID
There are two ways to get an image for your button:

• 🛒 Get it from the store
> https://create.roblox.com/store/category/2d <

• 📤 Using your own images
> https://create.roblox.com/dashboard/creations?activeTab=Decal <

To get the image ID, click “...” on the decal and select “Copy ID”, or copy it from the URL. To upload, use the Decals tab in the creations panel and get the ID from the Images tab.

==[=====================÷÷÷====================]==

Unibar Plus has two main button types (defined by the 'Type' parameter):
• "oneclick" – Single-action button
• "twoclick" – Toggle button: Selected / Deselected

⬇️ Below is how to create and use them correctly ⬇️

⚡ OneClick Button ⚡
• A oneclick button executes a function every time it is pressed.


💡 Examples of functions(With and without parameters) 💡  
  
function Kill()  
  print("Haha Killed!")  
end  
  
function Kill(player)  
  print(player .. " Killed!!")  
end  
  
(Without parameters)  
game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")["Unibar Plus API"].MakeButton:Fire("oneclick", "KillButton", "12345", Kill)  
  
(With parameters)  
game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")["Unibar Plus API"].MakeButton:Fire("oneclick","KillButton","12345",function() Kill("Jhon") end)  
  
This will create the button in the Unibar, and whenever it is clicked, it will execute the defined function.  

==[=====================÷÷÷====================]==

🔁 TwoClick Button (Toggle)

A twoclick button works like a toggle switch with two states:

• Selected – runs SelectedFunction
• Unselected – runs UnSelectedFunction


💡 Examples of functions(With and without parameters) 💡  
  
function TpVoid()  
  print("Bruh")  
end  
  
function TpLobby()  
  print("Lobby, wow")  
end  
  
function Kick(player)  
  print(player .. " kicked!!")  
end  
  
(Without parameters)  
game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")["Unibar Plus API"].MakeButton:Fire("twoclick","TpButton", "12345", "678910", TpLobby, TpVoid)  
  
(With parameters)  
game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")["Unibar Plus API"].MakeButton:Fire("twoclick","KillButton","12345","678910", function() Kick("Jhon") end, function() Kick("Alex") end)
  

❓ How it works:

• First click: Button becomes selected, runs SelectedFunction.
• Second click: Button becomes unselected, runs UnSelectedFunction.


==[=====================÷÷÷====================]==

🔔 Notifications

Displayed using the Notify event.

⚙️ Syntax:
game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")["Unibar Plus API"].Notify:Fire(title, text, duration)

Parameters:
title – Notification title
text – Notification message
duration – How long the notification stays visible


Example:
game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")["Unibar Plus API"].Notify:Fire("Wow", "Hey guys", 20)

==[=====================÷÷÷====================]==

🗑️ Remove Buttons

Removes a button previously created in Unibar:

game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")["Unibar Plus API"].RemoveButton:Fire("KillButton")

This will remove the button if it exists.

==[=====================÷÷÷====================]==

⚠️ Code Security

Unibar Plus automatically handles:

❌ Invalid functions
❌ Errors inside functions
❌ Incorrect use of the button creation function

If a function does not exist or produces an error, a Notify alert will appear when the button is clicked.

==[=====================÷÷÷====================]==

🧠 Examples Combining Everything

-- OneClick without parameters
game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")["Unibar Plus API"].MakeButton:Fire("oneclick", "LightButton", "101744283149050", TurnOnLight)

-- OneClick with parameters
game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")["Unibar Plus API"].MakeButton:Fire("oneclick", "MusicButton", "101744283149050", function() PlaySong("MySong") end)

-- TwoClick without parameters
game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")["Unibar Plus API"].MakeButton:Fire("twoclick", "TpButton", "12345", "678910", TpLobby, TpVoid)

-- TwoClick with parameters
game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")["Unibar Plus API"].MakeButton:Fire("twoclick", "KickButton", "12345", "678910", function() Kick("Jhon") end, function() Kick("Alex") end)

-- Notification
game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")["Unibar Plus API"].Notify:Fire("Wow", "Hey guys", 20)

-- Remove a button
game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")["Unibar Plus API"].RemoveButton:Fire("KickButton")

==[=====================÷÷÷====================]==

🚀 Summary

Unibar Plus provides 4 main features:

🔘 MakeButton (oneclick) – Executes a function when clicked
🔁 MakeButton (twoclick) – Creates toggle buttons with two states
🗑️ RemoveButton – Removes an existing button
🔔 Notify – Displays notifications

All features are designed to be simple, safe, and easy to integrate.
